Welkom police in the Free State are looking for the relatives of a man whose remains were found in 2015. The discovery of the body was made by a passerby in an open field behind a garage. The man was buried in a shallow grave and his bones were sticking out of the ground. Police spokesman Captain Stephen Thakeng said: “On 29 April 2015, Welkom police were informed of a human skeleton found in an open field next to Koppie Alleen Road. “Police attended to the scene and the remains were taken to the victim identification centre to help with facial reconstruction.” He was between 1,5m and 1,6m tall. Thakeng said anyone who might know the victim should contact Warrant Officer Kevin Douglas on 057 391 6261 during office.